        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 18 at 5:55PM CDT by NWS Shreveport LA</headline>
        <description>At 555 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 15
miles southwest of Jonesboro, moving southwest at 10 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts of 50 to 55 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is possible.

Locations impacted include...
Martin, Goldonna, Saline, Ashland, Chestnut and Creston.
</description>
        <instruction>Monitor the weather situation closely and be alert for threatening
weather conditions.

This storm may intensify, so be certain to monitor local radio
stations and available television stations for additional
information and possible warnings from the National Weather Service.</instruction>
